<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-07-0909 </DOCNO><TEXT>Using the methods of chemical analysis, IR spectroscopy and PMR of broadlines, regularities of Mo/sup 6+/ ion sorption by tin hydroxide are studied.Anionic exchange, resulting in the formation of surface compounds, containingmolybdenum in octahedral coordination, is found to be one of the reasonsfor molybdate-ion sorption in acid medium, where tin hydroxide possessesa higher absorption ability. The role of OH-groups and H/sub 2/O moleculesof hydroxide in the process of Mo/sup 6+/ ion sorption is shown.</TEXT></DOC>